@node play "The game: Installation/Playing"

                             Installation

  The installation is very simple, just place "Zeeconn" where you
want on your hard drive, floppy disk, Ram Disk, etc. No other files
or Libraries are needed. However, the game requires a 68020(+)
Amiga with Workbench 2.0 or higher.

                             How to play?

  To play, click on a coloured tile (or a small dot) that is
located diagonally between two other coloured tiles. If these two
tiles are of the same colour, a link of that colour will then be
created between the clicked tile and the same coloured tiles.
Otherwise, that link will have a 'neutral' colour.

  The clicked tile will be transformed to a small dot, which can
still be clicked on, so it can link other tiles, but it can no
longer serve as a coloured tile afterwards. The coloured tiles that
are linked can no longer be clicked on (if you click on one of
them, it will have no effect), however, they can still potentially
be linked to other coloured tiles...

  When you link tiles, you get 1 point for the neutral links and
10 points for links that connect tiles of the same colour.

  When it is no longer possible to link tiles together, the game
board is completed and the game will display a new board where you
will continue to link tiles together, and so on, until all game
boards have been played...

  Have fun!

  You can quit the game by clicking on the game window's close
button or by pressing on the 'Esc' key.

